`/apis/rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1/roles/` returns a `RoleList` object ("kind": "RoleList", "apiVersion": "rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1") and when apiserver omits the type meta (`kind` and `apiVersion`) for `items` when responding a list object (did a quick search but didn't find the reason behind).

Usually what happens is: 

```
GET host:port/api/v1/XXX

{
    "kind": "XXXList",
    "apiVersion": "v1",
    "metadata": {
        "selfLink": "/api/v1/XXX",
        "resourceVersion": "###"
    },
    "items": [
      {
        "metadata": ...
        "spec": ...
        "status": ...
      },
      {
        "metadata": ...
        "spec": ...
        "status": ...
      },
      {
        "metadata": ...
        "spec": ...
        "status": ...
      }
    ]
}
```

Therefore the `roles.items[0].kind` is `None`
